</section>
<section id="training-results" class="level1">
<h1>Training Results</h1>
<section id="performance-of-the-model" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="performance-of-the-model">Performance of the model</h2>
<p>The model performed well on unseen newspaper articles averaging 70% performance across all metrics:</p>
<ol type="1">
<li><p><strong>ENTS_P: <em>Precision score for named entities:</em></strong> measures the proportion of correctly identified named entities out of all predicted named entities. Higher values indicate better precision.</p></li>
<li><p><strong>ENTS_R: <em>Recall score for named entities:</em></strong> Recall measures the proportion of correctly identified named entities out of all actual named entities. Higher values indicate better recall.</p></li>
<li><p><strong>ENTS_F: <em>F1 score for named entities:</em></strong> measure of the model’s accuracy in identifying named entities, considering both precision and recall. Higher values indicate better performance.</p></li>
<li><p><strong>SCORE: <em>Represents an overall score:</em></strong> that combines multiple metrics to evaluate the performance of the NER pipeline. Higher values indicate better overall performance.</p></li>
</ol>
<div>

</div>
<div class="quarto-layout-panel" data-layout-ncol="1">
